        Official Singles Chart on 22/10/2021

        22 October 2021 - 28 October 2021

        The Official Singles Chart Top 100 reflects the UKs biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1. View the biggest songs of 2025.

        WEEKLY CHART REVIEW (22/10/2021 29/10/2021)

        (Negative)

        1) Purple Disco Machine doesnt appear to have made an impact on either chart this week! I thought Exotica & the tracks from it wouldve done a lot better, given how popular Daft Punk were on the charts & how similar his new album sounds to their signature style. I think this wouldve performed a lot better a few years ago when EDM was at its prime though, but I still expected better given the recent disco revival.

        2) Unless it somehow avoided this week, we look set to potentially lose Visiting Hours in the next chart thanks to ACR! Sure, its no Supermarket Flowers or Afire Love, but it still resonates with me on an emotional level & I dont even think the release of = will be enough to give this a second wind here.

        3) Speaking of ACR, thats what caused Lil Nas X to have a particularly bad week here, since both of his previous singles took massive drops & while you could argue that Montero had already got old, I was still loving seeing Industry Baby so high up every week! At least Thats What I Want is continuing to hang in there though.

        4) Starlight debuted so low this week! I know its difficult for older groups such as Westlife to get a big hit nowadays when almost all of their discographic buy rather than stream their music & its not the group nor their fans even care about their chart position anymore anyway when theyve proven so much already, but this is their best song in years & it deserved way better in my opinion.

        (Mixed)

        1) Cold Heart [PNAU Remix] is off the top spot after just one week! Its a little disappointing that it didnt stay there for longer, but Im just relieved that it managed to get there at all & its fine that it lost out to one of my favourite artists of the century, who Ill talk about a bit more later.

        2) My Heart Goes [La Di Da] just fell short of the Top 10 again! It mightve soured on me slightly thanks to the overplay & its definitely not among the best tracks from Becky Hills new album, but I still like it a lot.

        3) Both Happier Than Ever & No Time To Die fell for Billie this week! I kind of prepared myself for this all week because I knew it was going to happen, although its still disappointing to see. At least they had incredible chart runs though!

        4) Wasted finally seems to have crashed out! I cant put it in the positive section because of how it dropped off (coughACRcough!).

        (Positive)

        1) Completely unsurprisingly, Adeles straight in at #1 with her first single since 2016 & also to the surprise of absolutely nobody, I absolutely love it! Now, granted, this is a very predictable Adele heartbreak ballad & its nothing we havent heard from her before, although the lyrics seem to resonate more here given how much it reflects her recent personal life, involve the divorce from her ex-husband, along with the distance between Adele & her child because of it. Of course, the vocals are completely flawless because you all know that Adele is a powerhouse singer, while the thumping piano keys & subtle touches of bass are both features of this song that will make her sound even more passionate! If I had to make a nit-pick, it would be that we dont get a real climax here, especially when the final hook couldve built up to so much more, e.g. throwing in a backing choir for the ending, but you know what, at the end of the day, your thoughts on this song will be almost completely similar to Adele as an artist as a whole! I still hope that shell explore new territory when we get into the other singles & even the album tracks on 30, but when the charts have gone this long without a household name whos always stood out among her peers, Im not about to complain for one minute that shes back. Amazing song & I cant wait to hear whats to come in this new era!

        2) My Universe crept back into the Top 5 thanks to Coldplays new album! I wouldnt have expected a collaboration with them & BTS to work on paper, but it really does here.

        3) Better Days is still moving up! Ive always loved this song, but I relied on it a lot this week especially for personal reasons.

        4) Boyz took a big second week drop! Good, because like I said last week, this isnt a good fit for Jesy Nelson at all. For as much as she wanted to stray away from Little Mix for so long, she sounded so much better on the songs that she released as part of the group!

        5) Let Somebody Go gets a really good debut for an album track! I think we can all relate to having to cut ties with a loved one for the benefit of both people involved, but this track just hits really deep, probably because of the harmonies between Chris Martin & Selena Gomez on the second pre-chorus, as well as both of them nailing it with the vocals. The song closes with a sudden swell of instrumentation from the rest of the band grabs the listeners attention immediately, yet it doesnt feel too abrupt or out of place at the same time! Certainly a highlight from the album for me, the only thing that couldve beat it mightve been Coloratura charting with it (unlikely because of that song being over 10 minutes long), but hey, Ill take what I can get, especially when the quality is this high.

        6) As well as the #1 single, Adele also got two of her older hits to re-enter the Top 40! When We Were Young & Someone Like You are both amazing choices for the British public to stream again to celebrate her comeback! You know what? I might just end up doing the same this weekend!

        7) I knew it avoided ACR last week, but I wasnt expecting to Drive to start picking back up again like that! Does anyone know the reason behind it? Anyway, its an absolutely bop whatever caused it, haha.

        My latest personal chart (replace the * with an o): www.crownnote.c*m/charts/piran/pirans-top-50-12
